    "excerpt": "Critics weigh in on the films most likely to dominate the upcoming awards circuit.",
    "body": "With six months until the ceremony, the awards race is already taking shape. A handful of films have emerged as frontrunners, while several late-year releases could still disrupt the field.\n\nThe current favourite is a historical drama that premiered at Venice to rapturous reviews. The film combines the kind of sweeping narrative that voters love with the intimate character work that critics reward.\n\nClose behind is a contemporary drama that tackles social media and mental health with a directness that has divided audiences but united critics.\n\nThe dark horse is an independent film made for under $5 million that has grossed over $200 million worldwide. Its director would be the youngest person ever nominated for Best Director.\n\n'There's no obvious frontrunner,' one veteran awards consultant told us. 'Which makes it the most interesting race in years.'",
