    "title": "The Sequel Nobody Expected — First Look and Fan Reactions",
    "excerpt": "The franchise returns with a bold new direction. Here is everything we know so far.",
    "body": "When the original film was released seven years ago, it was conceived as a standalone story. There was no sequel clause, no post-credits tease, no franchise blueprint.\n\nSo when the same director announced a follow-up last summer, the reaction was a mixture of excitement and apprehension. Based on the footage we've seen, this sequel is not attempting to replicate the original.\n\n'The worst thing we could do is make the same film again,' the director told us. 'The characters have moved on. The world has moved on. The filmmaking should reflect that.'\n\nThe most significant change is structural. Where the original was a tightly contained thriller set over a single weekend, the sequel spans three decades and multiple continents.\n\nEarly test screenings have been polarising — which the director considers a positive sign. 'If everyone likes it, we haven't done our job.'",
