    "title": "Celebrity Street Style: The 25 Most Iconic Looks This Month",
    "excerpt": "Off-duty fashion from the stars — casual, bold, and endlessly re-pinnable.",
    "body": "Street style photography has always occupied an interesting space in celebrity culture. Unlike red carpet images, which are managed within an inch of their lives, street style captures something closer to genuine personal expression.\n\nThe reality, as our photographer discovered during a month of documenting celebrity street style across New York, Los Angeles, and London, is more nuanced. Even 'casual' celebrity dressing is a performance.\n\n'There's a calculation to it,' one stylist told us. 'When a client is photographed leaving a gym, they know the photos will be published. The outfit is chosen. The sunglasses are selected.'\n\nThat said, the best street style moments do reveal something genuine about the wearer. Our top twenty-five selections this month showcase a remarkable range.\n\nThe dominant trend this month was restraint. After years of logomania, the most interesting looks were the quietest — neutral palettes, clean silhouettes, and investment pieces that whispered rather than shouted.",
