    "cat": "INTERVIEW",
    "title": "Candid Conversations: Rising Stars on Fame, Pressure, and Authenticity",
    "excerpt": "Three breakout actors open up about the reality of sudden stardom.",
    "body": "The three actors sitting across from us in a Soho hotel suite have something in common beyond their youth and talent: each experienced a dramatic rise to fame within the past eighteen months.\n\n'Nobody prepares you for the loss of anonymity,' says the first. 'You go from being a person to being a product. People project their expectations onto you.'\n\nThe second nods in agreement. 'The hardest part isn't the work — the work is what I trained for. The hardest part is the stuff around the work. The social media scrutiny. The paparazzi.'\n\nThe third, the youngest at twenty-two, describes a different kind of pressure: the pressure to be grateful. 'Everyone tells you how lucky you are. And you are lucky. But gratitude doesn't make the anxiety go away.'\n\nDespite these challenges, all three express a deep commitment to their craft. 'I don't want to be famous,' says the first. 'I want to be good. The fame is just a side effect.'",
