    "excerpt": "A photographer's 12-month project capturing celebrities without the red-carpet armour.",
    "body": "The idea was simple: photograph the world's most famous people without the armour of styling and PR oversight. What photographer Elena Vasquez didn't expect was how willing they'd be to participate.\n\n'The first person I approached said yes within an hour,' Vasquez recalled. 'That never happens. But I think there's a hunger right now for something real.'\n\nThe resulting series features twenty subjects captured in moments of genuine unguardedness. Some are laughing. A few are visibly tired. One is crying. All are recognisably themselves.\n\nThe technical approach was deliberately stripped back. Natural light only. No post-production retouching. A single 50mm lens.\n\n'I wanted the images to feel like they were taken by a friend, not a professional,' she explained. The full series will be exhibited at the Saatchi Gallery in London this autumn.",
